  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Kasasiro Zaabu (Waste Is Gold)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Kasasiro Zaabu will improve the livelihoods of women and young people living in Kawempe, Kampala, by scaling up six early-stage plastic bottle recycling businesses. Through the project, businesses will be supported to scale up their operations through access to dedicated business loans as well as business training and mentoring. In turn, to support effective waste management, community members will be trained as waste recovery agents and educated on waste management and recycling, contributing directly to the work of the businesses through regular community-led clean-up activities.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project will indirectly benefit 67,140 members of the community, including directly benefiting 175 business group members, 90 waste recovery agents and 60 village health team members.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">To improve the livelihoods of women and youth and tackle poor waste management practices in the Kawempe Division of Kampala district.</narrative>
  </description>
